      "comment": "PAW GUSTO (6) goes very well this trip starting 10 times for four wins and two minors. Was out of placings last time (22.74) at Warrnambool in a Grade 5, finishing sixth and beaten 8 lengths. With a clean break looks hard to beat. PAW NATULLO (4) can keep on winning after strong last start success, claiming a Grade 5 at Ballarat over 390m in 22.17. Harder here but expected to measure up. LAMIA WHEEZE (7) has a strong record this trip with nine wins and four placings from 19 starts. Below best last time at Sandown (29.99) in a Free For All, finishing a 14 length sixth. Suited here and expected to run well. WINTER GOES (2) has a solid strike rate from this box.",
